<script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the median apartment price in Newstead?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Newstead apartment prices vary significantly by building, floor level and view line. Entry-level one-bedroom apartments are priced well below riverfront prestige stock, while premium two and three-bedroom apartments in sought-after buildings command a significant premium. The Gasworks precinct and riverfront proximity are the strongest price drivers. For a current assessment of a specific property, contact Daniel for a no-obligation appraisal." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take to sell an apartment in Newstead?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Well-positioned Newstead apartments with strong views, good floor plans and quality finishes typically sell within 20 to 40 days. Oversupply in certain building types and floor levels can extend that timeframe, which is why accurate pricing and targeted marketing to the right buyer profile makes a significant difference." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the lifestyle like in Newstead?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Newstead centres on the Gasworks precinct, a mixed-use destination with restaurants, bars, a cinema, a Farmers Market and retail anchored by Harris Farm. The Brisbane River Bikeway runs through the suburb and connects residents to New Farm Park, Teneriffe and the CBD. It attracts young professionals, downsizers and investors drawn to walkability and inner-city convenience." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Newstead a good suburb to sell in right now?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Newstead has matured significantly as a market. Demand from owner-occupiers, particularly downsizers and professionals, has strengthened the top end of the apartment market. Properties with genuine river views, large floorplates or proximity to the Gasworks continue to attract competitive buyer interest. Investor-grade stock in older buildings requires a more targeted approach." }
    }
  ]
})}</script>

