<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I understand this market. Newstead's apartment market is layered, building quality, floor level, view corridor and body corporate health all affect value in ways that a simple suburb median won't tell you. Positioning a Newstead property well means knowing which buyers are looking, what they're comparing it to, and how to differentiate it from the volume of stock that enters the market here each year.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Gasworks Plaza anchors the suburb's retail and lifestyle offer, with Harris Farm, a cinema and a consistently strong dining precinct drawing residents and visitors alike. The Farmers Market on Saturday mornings is a fixture for the community. The Brisbane River Bikeway along the foreshore connects Newstead directly to Teneriffe, New Farm Park and the CBD, making car-free commuting genuinely practical. Buyers competing for properties here are predominantly professionals, downsizers and investors seeking yield in a supply-constrained premium pocket.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
